bst.js

A pure JavaScript implementation of a binary search tree.

Summary
bst.jsA pure JavaScript implementation of a binary search tree.
BSTThe binary search tree class.
Functions
searchSearch through a binary tree.
insertInsert into a binary tree.
traverseCall a function on each node of a binary tree.
minFind the key of the node with the lowest key number.
maxFind the key of the node with the highest key number.
successorFind the key that successes the root node.
predecessorFind the key that preceeds the root node.
rootThe key of the root node.

BST

The binary search tree class.

Functions

search

search: function (key)

Search through a binary tree.

Parameters

keythe key to search for.

Returns

the value of the found node, or null if no node was found, or undefined if no key was specified.

insert

insert: function (key,
value)

Insert into a binary tree.

Parameters

keythe key to search for.
valuethe value to associate with the key (any type of object).

Returns

true, or undefined if no key was specified.

traverse

traverse: function (callback)

Call a function on each node of a binary tree.

Parameters

callbackthe function to call on each node, this function takes a key and a value as parameters.  If no callback is specified, print is called.

Returns

true.
